<p><a name="Tabulated_exposure_values" id="Tabulated_exposure_values"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Exposure_value&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Tabulated exposure values">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Tabulated exposure values</span></h2>
<p>An exposure meter may not always be available, and using a meter to determine exposure for some scenes with unusual lighting distribution may be difficult. However, natural light, as well as many scenes with artificial lighting, is predictable, so that exposure often can be determined with reasonable accuracy from tabulated values.</p>
<dl>
<dd><b>Table 2. Exposure values (ISO 100 speed) for various lighting conditions</b><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></dd>
</dl>
<dl>
<dd>
<table class="wikitable" style="text-align: left">
<tr>
<th>Lighting Condition</th>
<th>EV<sub style="font-size: 70%">100</sub></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2">Daylight</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.1em 0.5em;">Light sand or snow in full or slightly hazy sunlight (distinct shadows)<sup>a</sup></td>
<td style="text-align: center; padding: 0.1em 0.5em;">16</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.1em 0.5em;">Typical scene in full or slightly hazy sunlight (distinct shadows)<sup>a,b</sup></td>
<td style="text-align: center; padding: 0.1em 0.5em;">15</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 0.1em 0.5em;">Typical scene in hazy sunlight (soft shadows)</td>
<td style="text-align: center; padding: 0.1em 0.5em;">14</td>
</tr>
